The '''Psi Defender''' is the third of the three core [[Psi-Tech]] modules in the [[HelmKit]] psi-bay. Engineering-honestly, it is a near-field RF anomaly detector with adaptive nulling; doctrinally, it is a defensive shield against directed [[Psionic Warfare|psionic weapons]] and ambient [[Psionic Defenses|psychic attacks]]. It is shield, not sword: it does not radiate offensive countermeasures, and it does not deny psi-space to bystanders. It hardens the operator locally.

{{Defensive-publication}}

== Overview ==

The Defender operates passively most of the time, escalating only on detection. Three engagement layers:

* '''Detect.''' Continuous near-field RF + magnetometer + electrostatic monitoring. Signatures classified against the [[Psionic Threat Model]] library.
* '''Log.''' Every detection (signature, vector estimate, time, location) is recorded for after-action review.
* '''Counter.''' On confirmed-class signature, the Defender drives a counter-pattern through the same coil substrate used by the [[Psi Stabilizer]]. The counter-pattern is computed to ''locally'' cancel the intrusion at the wearer's body, not to broadcast a jamming signal.

Operational uses: hostile-environment ops; [[StarCom]] operator protection during high-coherence sessions; long-duration field deployments where threat exposure is plausible.

== Theoretical Basis ==

The Defender sits on a deliberately layered stack so that ''the detector is useful even if the psionic interpretation is wrong'':

* {{Psi-claim
| status = PROVISIONAL
| cites = [[Geomagnetic Sensitivity in Humans]]
| methods = Multiple converging studies; replication still in progress.
| falsifier = Pre-registered, multi-site replication returning a null result (Bayes factor &le; 1/3).
| confidence = medium
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} Anomalous near-field RF, magnetic, and electrostatic environments are detectable with commodity sensors. This is the Defender's base utility — operators ''should'' know when they are walking through an unusual EM environment, psi-related or not.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = TESTABLE
| cites = [[Resonant Neurobiology]]
| methods = Concrete protocol defined; replication not yet attempted.
| falsifier = A blinded study following the proposed protocol returning a null result at p < 0.01.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} Operators perform measurably worse (HRV-coherence, reaction time, decision accuracy) in some classes of EM-anomalous environments. This is falsifiable: instrument operators, log environments, statistically test.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = SPECULATIVE
| cites = [[Psi Field]], [[Scalar Electromagnetic Waves]]
| methods = Theoretical; not yet operationalised into a testable protocol.
| falsifier = Quantitative prediction shown to conflict with established physics or biology.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} A subset of those environments are ''directed psi'' — hostile, coherent, targeted. The Defender's pattern-matching classifier is trained on what the Clan's [[Psionic Threat Model]] catalogues. This is the doctrinal claim; the detector remains useful at the base layer regardless.
* {{Psi-claim
| status = SPECULATIVE
| cites = [[Psi Field]]
| methods = Theoretical; not yet operationalised into a testable protocol.
| falsifier = Quantitative prediction shown to conflict with established physics or biology.
| confidence = low
| last_reviewed = 2026-05-12
}} A counter-pattern at the wearer's body cancels the intrusion as a field-theoretic interference effect. This is the deeper interpretation of the counter mode; engineering-honest framing is "adaptive nulling against a measured local field".

== Subsystems and BOM ==

=== Mk0 ''Symbolic Defender'' (target ≤ $40) ===

* 3D-printed module shell + sigil plate — $10
* WS2812B status ring — $3
* ATtiny85 — $2
* Cold-cast brass-pigment sigil — $10
* Hardware + decals — $5

No detection, no emission. Works through operator vigilance and intentional practice. Brand-and-ritual carrier.

=== Mk1 ''Bench Defender'' (target ≤ $350) ===

* HackRF One (or LimeSDR Mini) as broadband front-end — $100
* nRF52840 (compute + BLE) — $15
* HMC5883L magnetometer ×2 (for vector estimate) — $16
* Electrostatic probe (DIY op-amp + plate) — $5
* Bifilar coil (shared substrate with [[Psi Stabilizer]]) — $5
* SI5351 + Class-D amp + low-pass — $14
* Single 18650 + TP4056 + boost — $10
* Enclosure, connectors, USB-C — $25
* Reference signature library (SD card / flash) — $5

Software: real-time STFT + matched-filter against the [[Psionic Threat Model]] signature library; classifier output → MCU-B → counter-pattern dispatch (only if class above threshold).

=== Mk2 / Mk3 ===

Mk2 adds: multi-antenna direction-finding (vector estimate sharpened from monopole to coarse bearing), multi-operator coordinated shielding via [[NavCom]] mesh share (each operator broadcasts what they detect to the rest of the team), persistent threat database. Mk3 adds: integration with the [[Psi-Tech]] triad and the [[PsiNet]] threat-feed.

== Build Notes ==

* '''Detector first.''' Build and validate detection in real environments (urban EM, industrial, transit, rural baseline) before any counter mode. Most of the field-utility is in the detect-and-log function; the counter mode is the speculative layer.
* '''No outbound jamming.''' The counter coil is the same near-field substrate as the [[Psi Stabilizer]] — short-range only. There is no broadcast antenna. This is enforced by physical antenna selection, not just firmware.
* '''Signature library curation.''' Every signature added to the classifier requires (a) a documented capture, (b) at least one repeat observation, (c) a [[Psionic Threat Model]] entry. No "vibes-based" signatures.
* '''Class thresholds.''' Default: classify-only below medium confidence; counter only at high confidence; log everything. Tunable per-operator.

== Safety and Ethics ==

* All emission limits per [[HelmKit Architecture]] and ICNIRP near-field basic restriction − 6 dB.
* '''No retaliation, ever.''' The Defender is doctrinally and physically incapable of offensive emission. The counter coil is a near-field nulling coil; it cannot project a useful signal to a third party.
* Multi-operator share is information-only (signature + vector estimate); no remote-command of one operator's Defender by another.
* Logging is local-only by default; export requires operator action.
* [[Tho'ra Mission Doctrine]]: shield, not sword.

