== Failure Modes and Mitigations ==

* '''False-positive classification → unwanted counter mode.''' → Default threshold high; counter mode is opt-in per-operator; every counter event logs full feature vector for review.
* '''Stuck-on counter emit.''' → MCU-B independent watchdog; auto-cut after fixed dwell; thermal cutout on coil.
* '''Signature library poisoning.''' → Library is signed and curated; entries require [[Psionic Threat Model]] documentation; no remote auto-update.
* '''Mistaking benign EM for hostile psi.''' → Multi-sensor cross-check (RF + magnetometer + electrostatic must agree above threshold); ambiguous cases log without action.
* '''Operator over-reliance.''' → The Defender supplements vigilance; it does not replace it. Briefing material is explicit.
* '''Retaliation pressure.''' → The hardware is incapable of meaningful offensive emission; the doctrine forbids it; logs make any policy violation visible.

